Re: Bathroom humor
by Mike Cash » Sat 07.04.2009 6:01 am Hyperworm wrote:I think your translation is right but your interpretation is wrong.I think the 詰まりの原因 is politely omitted, and could be represented in a translation by "it"."Please flush after use, because [otherwise] it causes (the toilet) to get clogged"Perhaps, above a urinal is the wrong place for this sign...??But as written the sign technically indicates that flushing is the cause of the pipes getting clogged up (and that such clogging is the desired outcome). Of course, no one is stupid enough to misinterpret the intended message of the sign in such a nonsensical way. I asked a couple of native speakers to verify my gaijin suspicion that I had found the construction of the sentence was odd, and got an 言われてみれば reaction.
Never underestimate my capacity for pettiness.
Mike Cash
Posts: 2737Joined: Sun 08.20.2006 3:38 am
