Re: Bathroom humor
by keatonatron » Sun 07.05.2009 9:11 am Yudan Taiteki wrote:I don't really see anything wrong with the current reading since the meaning is obvious, but another way would be 使用後必ず水を流して下さい。そうしないと、詰まるおそれがあります or something like that.Actually, using おそれがあります is a good one. You don't need そうしないと with it though.詰まりのおそれがありますので、使用後水を流して下さい。Anyway, I saw another sign today that I thought wouldn't be acceptable in Western culture.And this one was actually done professionally! (not a simple computer printout)
Searching for models and actors in Tokyo. No experience required!
